data.whatILove:
A note from the Seller: 

Dear Home Buyers: 

Three years ago, I was a single mom searching for a home with a basement for my growing teens to hang out with their friends. I had looked in many parts of the city but kept hoping something would open up here in Auburn Springs. When this house became available, I only looked at it once before making an offer and still talk about how lucky I was to get it after a bidding war. The house had all the things my children and I wanted most on our wish list:  a gas stove and double oven in the kitchen, lots of storage, a laundry room by the master bedroom and a yard for my son to play lacrosse. But it also had nearly everything else we hoped for; a wonderful kitchen that looks into the family room, plenty of space for family get-togethers, and a bonus bedroom downstairs for guests to stay over. We had many wonderful parties out back by the firepit; there’s room for a crowd. Laughter and good food were enjoyed while the kids caught lightning bugs and played flashlight tag. The surrounding neighbors are all such good people. Halloween is always spectacular in our neighborhood. Many times my kids would come home with two bags full of candy. The annual Popsicle Parade on the Fourth of July has always started in the park. Aside from our house, we are going to miss the neighborhood. We are close to a couple of fabulous restaurants (be sure to try the cocktails & shrimp at 1933!), our favorite golf course is only a half-mile away, and the kids can walk to the elementary school as well as Fishers Junior High. This has been a home filled with love and we wish you, the next owners, the same good fortune. Welcome Home!  **** CALL/TEXT: 317-410-0505 TO SCHEDULE PROPERTY TOUR  ****
